@NODE "Mail_0" " Re: HD Trouble "
From: Lloyd Rosen <seasons@softhome.net>
Date: 09-05-99 23:11:00
Subject: @{b}Re: HD Trouble@{ub}

From: "Lloyd Rosen" <seasons@softhome.net>

>From: Laura Vance <vancel@amiga.nols.com>

>There is a program on AmiNet that will get your RDB information.  I had
>that same problem happen a few months ago.  I am using a 10GB hard drive
>and for some reason the format command messed up the RDB.  But it messed it
>up because I was still using my compuer whil it was formatting another
>partition on my drive.  

>Anyway, go on AmiNet and do a search for RDB.  I think disksalv works, but
>I don't think that it will actually restore your RDB.  You have to write
>down what the RDB is and re-input it in a program like "HDToolbox".

>Once I re-input the RDB info, I got all of my partitions back, except for
>the ones that I messed with the wrong way.  On those, I also had to use an
>undelete utility.

>Laura

Ok I give it a shot (though it states it wont work correctly on
non-dos partitions (pfs))

Thanks for tip,

  Lloyd Rosen,          <seasons@softhome.net>
  Seasons               <http://listen.to/floydmon>


@ENDNODE
