@NODE "Mail_2" " Re: Barfly v2 & VBCC "
From: Andrew Bell <andrew.ab2000@bigfoot.com>
Date: 09-06-99 18:03:11
Subject: @{b}Re: Barfly v2 & VBCC@{ub}

From: Andrew Bell <andrew.ab2000@bigfoot.com>

Hi David,

On 05-Sep-99, you wrote:

> I downloaded Barfly and its exactly what I want. However, I have a
> problem when trying to debug code compiled with VBCC. I've compiled
> the code with "vc -k -g test.c -o test". I can get Barfly to load
> the file and the source window comes up with the disassembled source
> for the program. However, I can't get it to load the symbol hunk or
> display the source in C. I don't know if the debug info is in the
> final executable, but it appears to be in the .o file.

The debug information is normally stored within the executable itself.
I tested VBCC with some example source code, but I was unable to get it to produce line debug blocks, try mailing the author of VBCC. I'm sure
he'll be able to provide you with more information, if such a feature
does exist.

You can only open the source window in BDebug if the executable
contains line debug blocks.

Regards, Andrew Bell.
-- 

