@NODE "Mail_7" " console.device bug and rom ripping! "
From: Dominic Clifton <dom@dsltd.force9.co.uk>
Date: 09-07-99 13:42:28
Subject: @{b}console.device bug and rom ripping!@{ub}

From: Dominic Clifton <dom@dsltd.force9.co.uk>


Is it me, or on an 8 colour screen the ANSI escape sequence
<esc>[0m should return the foreground (text) colour to 7 (white) and
not 1 (red) ?

Is it possible to fix this by way of patching the console device ?

How do you grab a shared library or device from the rom so that you
can patch it to make a disk based version (under a different name or not) ?

-- 

