@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_10" " Re: datatype transparancy "
From: Rod Schnell <rodsch@telusplanet.net>
Date: 09-07-99 23:37:41
Subject: @{b}Re: datatype transparancy@{ub}

From:	Rod Schnell <rodsch@telusplanet.net>

Hello Allan

On 07-Sep-99, Allan Odgaard wrote:
> From: Allan Odgaard <Duff@DIKU.DK>
> 
> On 30-Aug-99, Rod Schnell wrote:
> 
>>> This is definetely not what my tests nor experience has told me. I'd
>>> strongly recommend to install those datatypes from Gunther Nikl which can
>>> be
>> Which one's are Gunther's? His name rings a bell, so I've probably looked
>> at
> 
> I think they all have 'v43' appended to their name. Have a look in
> util/dtype/ at Aminet.

Thanks. BTW, regarding ak- datatypes, I did some checking. Nothing is crippled
or disabled and progress bars can be turned off in prefs regardless of whether
you're registered or not. I'm not registered and I have them turned off.

According to the docs, the only thing 'registration' does is put the word
"registered" in the progress bar and the reason it does that is because those
who did 'register' wanted it. :)

  Rod


