@NODE "Mail_14" " Using Datatypes "
From: Laura Vance <vancel@amiga.nols.com>
Date: 09-10-99 01:08:43
Subject: @{b}Using Datatypes@{ub}

From: Laura Vance <vancel@amiga.nols.com>

Hello,

I have been trying for a few days now to get my program to use datatypes. 
This is the first time that I've attempted to use them, and I want to go
from the current situation of having all graphics internal as C source code
to having external files that can be swapped to change how the program
looks.

The way that I've gathered to use the datatypes is the following sequence:

NewDTObject()
// create the window that will be used for output
if(object)
{
    AddDTObject()
    DoDTMethod()        // can I do more than one method per statement?
    RefreshDTObjectA()
}
else
{
    //get the error status from IoErr()
}
// do other stuff
RemoveDTObject()
// close the display window
DisposeDTObject()


I do not get any errors in my actual code, but the image isn't displayed. 
Do I have to do the "DoDTMethod()" function to get the image to display
itself in the window?  If not, what else do I need to do, or what do I need
to do differently?  I can post the actual code if anyone really wants to
see it, or I can send that section of code via email.

Laura


-- 
      \|/
     (o o)
---ooO(_)Ooo---
   Peekaboo!!



@ENDNODE
