First off, let me say thank you for at least showing me the sequence of the
commands, it seems that nothing that I've found can do that.  And all of
the examples on those sites show how to create datatypes, not necessarily
how to use them. (at least those are the only ones that I've found with
source code)

Second, I get some strange results with each of those two methods.  When I
tried the first method, using AddDTObject() and no DoDTMethod() statement,
the graphic would not render.  I added two lines before the RefreshDTObjectA() statement and it started working.  The reason I can't
leave those two lines in there is that the first one assigns the text to an
IntuiText structure and the second line is AutoRequest().  I put them in
there for debugging purposes, to make sure that the program was still
hitting that section of code.  When I saw it put the graphic in my window,
I immediately commented out those two lines.... and the graphic would not
display in my window anymore.  Put them back, it works, take them out, it
doesn't.... very consistently too.

With the second method, I think that something is happening with my BitMap
structure... This seems to be the case, because when I change the section
of code to get the attributes of the struct BitMap *, I will get a guru on
the GetDTAttrs() function and on the BltBitMapRastPort() function.  And the
graphic still doesn't display in my window.  This time, even adding the
AutoRequest() function doesn't kick it into gear.

So, I'm a little stuck, because I am very sure that it works for your
system, and I don't know why it wouldn't work for mine.... very confusing.


****UPDATE****

I 
ust wanted to try it one more time to make sure that these were still the
problem, and I was going through my code, commenting out the pertinent
lines, and uncommenting other lines, and instead of changing this
statement:

    if(GetDTAttrs(pics, DTA_NominalHoriz, &width,
                        DTA_NominalVert,  &height,
                        TAG_DONE) == 2)

to this:

    GetDTAttrs(pics, DTA_NominalHoriz, &width,
                     DTA_NominalVert,  &height,
                     TAG_DONE);// == 2)
in order to avoid just commenting out part of that line, I opted to change
it to this:

    GetDTAttrs(pics, DTA_NominalHoriz, &width,
                     DTA_NominalVert,  &height);
//                     TAG_DONE) == 2)

so that I have all of my comments highly visible from the left edge of the
window (mainly for printout purposes), basically I forgot to re-include the
"TAG_DONE" and all of a sudden, it works.... still strange, but as long as
it works without a GURU error, I'm happy  (c:

Just thought I'd still let you know what errors I was getting, and what
happened to fix them in case anyone else is having a similar problem.

Thanks for your help with the sequencing of commands.

Laura

PS. I know that it shouldn't make a difference with or without the 
    TAG_DONE, and if it's going to work one way and not the other, it
should
    work _with_ the TAG_DONE and not without it.... which is what keeps it
    strange even after it's working for me.

