From: "Harry J. Miktarian" <im007@jps.net>
Date: 09-13-99 06:29:01
Subject: @{b}SAS C++ and enforcer hits...@{ub}

From: "Harry J. Miktarian" <im007@jps.net>

Hello everybody,

  I'm taking a C++ class for giggles (work is paying for it :).  I'm using
SAS C/C++ as my compiler.  Can anybody tell me why the executable from this
simple piece of code is throwing up enforcer hits?  It is compiled with the
default scoptions except debug=symbolflush.  I'm using the latest SAS and
the latest (last) C++ beta from Steves site.

// Simple cash register program 
// Harry J. Miktarian & Ian Sedigh
// CS 201
// Project 1

#include <iostream.h>
#include <iomanip.h>

void main()

{

    double meal,total,tendered,change;
    const double tax=0.0825;

    cout <<"Please enter the price of the meal: ";
    cin >> meal;
    total = meal + (meal * tax);
    cout <<"\nYour total including tax is: "<<total <<endl;
    cout <<"\nPlease enter the amount tendered: ";
    cin >> tendered;
    change = tendered - total;
    cout <<"\n---------------------------------------"<<endl;
    cout.precision(2);
    cout.setf(ios::fixed | ios::showpoint);
    cout <<"The amount tendered is: "<<setw(15)<<tendered <<endl;
    cout <<"The cost of your meal was: "<<setw(12)<<total <<endl;
    cout <<"Your change will be: "<<setw(18) <<change <<endl;
    
}

-- 
                                     Kind Regards,

                                    Harry Miktarian




