@NODE "Mail_26" " Re: SAS C++ and enforcer hits... "
From: Michael_Sage@May-Co.com
Date: 09-13-99 14:10:00
Subject: @{b}Re: SAS C++ and enforcer hits...@{ub}

From: Michael_Sage@May-Co.com




> I seem to remember returning void from main is undefined. From nothing to
> sumoning an unpleasant man with a fork. Though I could be wrong.

Yes, I've run into this on our mainframe.  How implicit exits are handled by the
compiler is up to the compiler writer.  The best thing to do is define main() as
returning an int and add an exit(0) as the last statement.






