@NODE "Mail_34" " An interesting problem "
From: Serge Tumanyan <tumanyan@chat.ru>
Date: 09-15-99 21:44:24
Subject: @{b}An interesting problem@{ub}

From: Serge Tumanyan <tumanyan@chat.ru>

Hello, list.

I've found a strange problem. I have two files:

=== Cut ===
#include<...>  //here we include everything nessesary...

void myprocess(void);

void main(void)
  {  <...>
     pr=CreateNewProc(NP_Entry,myprocess,TAG_DONE);
     <...>
  }
=== Cut ===

=== Cut ===
#include<...>  //here we include everything nessesary...

class myclass
  {  myclass(void);
     ~myclass(void);
  };

myclass::myclass(void)
  {  <...>
     printf("Constructor finished\n");
     <...>
  }
myclass::~myclass(void)
  {  <...>
     printf("Destructor finished\n");
     <...>
  }

void myprocess(void)
  {  myclass temp;
     <...>
  }
=== Cut ===

The problem is the following: I expect the output like this:
Constructor finished
Destructor finished
but I get the following:
Constructor finished
Destructor finished
Destructor finished
and everything crashes. Where am I wrong? I use SAS/C 6.58. BTW, if I simply
call myprocess() everything is OK. Why???

