@NODE "Mail_35" " Re: Code formating tools "
From: Allan Odgaard <Duff@DIKU.DK>
Date: 09-15-99 22:29:55
Subject: @{b}Re: Code formating tools@{ub}

From: Allan Odgaard <Duff@DIKU.DK>

On 15-Sep-99, Christian Hattemer wrote:

> I've been playing around with Indent a litte. It produces quite nice
> results [...]

hrmpf...

> if (foo)
>   if (bar)
>      printf("This code sucks!");

> Is there already something which does this? I thought about doing it myself
> but it doesn't seem to be that simple as it should also handle the above
> code.

I don't think it's so complicated, just do a recursive function a la:

VOID CheckLine (STRPTR line)
{
   ULONG indent;
   puts(line);
   if(indent = CheckFor_if_while_do_Etc(line))
   {
      line = GetNextLine();
      if(strchr(line, "{");
      {
         puts(line);
      }
      else
      {
         IndentedOut("{", indent);
         CheckLine(line);
         IndentedOut("}", indent);
      }
   }
}

VOID main ()
{
   ...
   while(line = GetNextLine())
      CheckLine(line);
   ...
}

Regards Allan
