@NODE "Mail_62" " Re: Asl Screen mode requester "
From: Adrien HEMERY <iliak_@club-internet.fr>
Date: 09-22-99 11:32:36
Subject: @{b}Re: Asl Screen mode requester@{ub}

From: Adrien HEMERY <iliak_@club-internet.fr>

Hello Colin

> Looks like you have the same trouble I did,   check the header
> before you send it.

> It appears ONELIST server hates anything other than
> plain/text,    it certainly has a haemorage over Base64.....

Yep, so i'll rewrite it =:)

I want to open an asl sceen mode requester. But the problem is that i want it to filter screen modes... I looked at the autodic and found that :

    ASLSM_FilterFunc (struct Hook *) - A function to call for each mode
            encountered. If the function returns TRUE, the mode is
            included in the file list, otherwise it is rejected
            and not displayed. The function receives the following
            parameters:
                A0 - (struct Hook *)
                A1 - ULONG mode id
                A2 - (struct ScreenModeRequester *)
            (V38)

    So, what is a Hook and how can put it in my code ? I want the asl requester to *only* display screen mode with 8 bits depth, and one of the 3 following resolution :
        320x240
        320x256
        640x480

    Can some one mail a piece of code plz ??



Regards
-- 
Common sense is the collection of prejudices acquired by age eighteen.
-- Albert Einstein



