@NODE "Mail_64" " Re: Asl Screen mode requester "
From: Tim Hanson <msinister@connectfree.co.uk>
Date: 09-22-99 21:58:29
Subject: @{b}Re: Asl Screen mode requester@{ub}

From: Tim Hanson <msinister@connectfree.co.uk>

Adrien HEMERY wrote this on 22-Sep-99 at 11:32:36
 Hi Adrien 

-> Yep, so i'll rewrite it =:)
-> 
-> I want to open an asl sceen mode requester. But the problem is that i want
-> it to filter screen modes... I looked at the autodic and found that :
-> 
->    ASLSM_FilterFunc (struct Hook *) - A function to call for each mode
->            encountered. If the function returns TRUE, the mode is
->            included in the file list, otherwise it is rejected
->            and not displayed. The function receives the following
->            parameters:
->                A0 - (struct Hook *)
->                A1 - ULONG mode id
->                A2 - (struct ScreenModeRequester *)
->            (V38)
-> 
->    So, what is a Hook and how can put it in my code ? I want the asl
-> requester to *only* display screen mode with 8 bits depth, and one of the 3
-> following resolution :
->        320x240
->        320x256
->        640x480



If you look further down through the autodoc you`ll see lots of tags starting
ASLSM_. These include ASLSM_MinWidth and ASLSM_MaxWidth and ones for height
and depth. Problem is I think that the function might be broken as I can
never get it to work properly. Does anyone else suffer from this problem?


-- 
      
Tim Hanson,
by the River,Canterbury, Kent.
