@NODE "Mail_69" " Re: Asl Screen mode requester "
From: Rod Schnell <rodsch@telusplanet.net>
Date: 09-23-99 19:22:32
Subject: @{b}Re: Asl Screen mode requester@{ub}

From:	Rod Schnell <rodsch@telusplanet.net>

Hello Adrien

On 22-Sep-99, Adrien HEMERY wrote:
> From: Adrien HEMERY <iliak_@club-internet.fr>
> 
> I want to open an asl sceen mode requester. But the problem is that i want
> it to filter screen modes... I looked at the autodic and found that :
> 
>    ASLSM_FilterFunc (struct Hook *) - A function to call for each mode
>            encountered. If the function returns TRUE, the mode is
>            included in the file list, otherwise it is rejected
>            and not displayed. The function receives the following
>            parameters:
>                A0 - (struct Hook *)
>                A1 - ULONG mode id
>                A2 - (struct ScreenModeRequester *)
>            (V38)
> 
>    So, what is a Hook and how can put it in my code ? I want the asl

A hook is function that gets called to add functionality to libraries,
devices, applications etc. For more information on hooks in general, see
RKRM libraries, page 875.

> requester to *only* display screen mode with 8 bits depth, and one of the 3
> following resolution :
>        320x240
>        320x256
>        640x480
> 
>    Can some one mail a piece of code plz ??

Untested, but as long as I didn't make any silly typos, the following should
work (at least with SAS/C). You'll have to add code to check depth/resolution
and return TRUE/FALSE as appropriate.

/* This function gets called whenever a new screen mode is about to be
 * added to to the list in a screen mode requester. It lets an application
 * filter out entries it doesn't want. You can query the display database
 * using the provided mode id to decide whether you want this entry added to
 * the list or not. Return TRUE if the entry should be added, return FALSE
 * otherwise.
 */
static ULONG __asm ScreenModeFilter(register __a0 struct Hook *hook,
                                    register __a2 struct ScreenModeRequester
*smr,
                                    register __a1 ULONG modeID)
{
    kprintf("ScreenModeFilter(): mode is id 0x%08lx\n",modeID);
    return(TRUE);
}

/* declare hook */

struct Hook filterHook;

/* setup hook for use */

filterHook.h_Entry = (ULONG (*)())ScreenModeFilter;
filterHook.h_SubEntry = NULL;
filterHook.h_Data = NULL;


Then you just pass the hook's address into your screenmode requester.

ASLSM_FilterFunc, &filterHook,


  Rod


@ENDNODE
