Subject: @{b}Re: Iliak :(@{ub}

From: Allan Odgaard <Duff@DIKU.DK>

On 23-Sep-99, Adrien HEMERY wrote:

> Is there a (better) way to do it ?

Now exactly what is it you want to do? If you have a window then you should use
IDCMP, unless of course the input is for a specific object in your window then
you should look into adding a boopsi gadget which implements GM_HANDLEINPUT...

If you don't have a window then adding a custom cx object is probably the best
thing - this will be invoked for all input events, you can also set up cx
objects for specific events...

Regards Allan
