@NODE "Mail_95" " Using datatypes to get an 24bit array from any given picture? "
From: Fritsch Alexander <Alexander.Fritsch@icn.siemens.de>
Date: 09-28-99 15:10:42
Subject: @{b}Using datatypes to get an 24bit array from any given picture?@{ub}

From: Fritsch Alexander <Alexander.Fritsch@icn.siemens.de>

Hello,
I am writing a program witch processes a 24 bit picture. Its a cli-only
program and has no graphical output.
At the moment I use a sequnce like

myprog testpic.bmp

Testpic.bmp is a 24 bit w*nd*ws bitmap-picture. (Shame on me!) 
So I have to convert a picture to a 24bit-bmp file first.

I wonder whether it is possible to use datatypes to be able to use other
picture-types directly. Inside my program I need 24 bit rgb-data.
Can I use datatypes? Can I access the picture data from my program and in
whitch format I will get them? Do datatypes do a 24 bit-conversion for me or
would this still remain my job to do?

Could anybody give me hint witch steps I will have to do?

Kind regards Alexander Fritsch

@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_96" " Re: Using datatypes to get an 24bit array from any given picture? "
From: Nicholas Clarke <nclarke@diku.dk>
Date: 09-28-99 15:54:17
Subject: @{b}Re: Using datatypes to get an 24bit array from any given picture?@{ub}

From: Nicholas Clarke <nclarke@diku.dk>

On Tue, 28 Sep 1999, Fritsch Alexander wrote:

> From: Fritsch Alexander <Alexander.Fritsch@icn.siemens.de>
> Testpic.bmp is a 24 bit w*nd*ws bitmap-picture. (Shame on me!) 
> So I have to convert a picture to a 24bit-bmp file first.

No comment.

> I wonder whether it is possible to use datatypes to be able to use other
> picture-types directly. Inside my program I need 24 bit rgb-data.
> Can I use datatypes? Can I access the picture data from my program and in
> whitch format I will get them? Do datatypes do a 24 bit-conversion for me or
> would this still remain my job to do?

The normal datatypes from cbm don't support >8bit. But if you have a
gfxcard you have probably upgraded datatypes.library / picture.datatype /
gif,jpeg,iff,.../datatypes.

You should be able to find all those on aminet.

Depends what you mean by directly? Datatypes are supposed to encapsulate
the format specific data and supply a uniform interface to the different
storage formats.

I have no idea if non 24bit pictures are converted to 24bit for you if
thats what you want but its fairly easy to convert a bitmap once its
decoded.

> Could anybody give me hint witch steps I will have to do?

Sheep?

You could also wait for Allan Odgaard to finish his imagemanager library
project.

/ngc

