@NODE "Mail_101" " Re: Default non-proportional font "
From: Ben Hutchings <womble@zzumbouk.demon.co.uk>
Date: 09-29-99 23:45:41
Subject: @{b}Re: Default non-proportional font@{ub}

From: Ben Hutchings <womble@zzumbouk.demon.co.uk>

On Wed, Sep 29, 1999 at 09:23:02PM +0200, Damir Arh wrote:
> From: "Damir Arh" <damir.arh@guest.arnes.si>
> 
> Hello
> 
> I am writing a program in which I will need a non-proportional font as well
> as a proportional font. I already use the screen default font as a
> proportional font, but which font should I use as a default non-proportional
> font? Is there any way to obtain user's preferences on this subject? Or is
> there a specific font which I should use in this case?

The `system font' is always non-proportional.  This is the font
initially selected on new RastPorts, and you can also find it as
GfxBase->DefaultFont.

