What you need is a wee program which changes the boot priority of your
partitions and then resets, booting up from the HD with the highest
priority.
Probably not too difficult to write.
I wass going to suggest to change the priority with HDTools, but you'd have
to bootup first and its only convenient if you were to keep booting from a
particular partition for a prolonged period of time.


Yours, etc etc.
